---
description: Project context and lessons-learned workflow
globs: "*"
---

- Before major architecture, debugging, or planning work, read `.cursor/project-context/` and `.cursor/lessons-learned/` when relevant. Also read root `MEMORY.md` only if it exists in a target project.
- Store stable project state, architecture decisions, active plans, and workflow conventions in `.cursor/project-context/`.
- Store reusable bug lessons, CI failures, repeated-failure fixes, and debugging postmortems in `.cursor/lessons-learned/`.
- In this template repository, prefer `.cursor/project-context/decisions.md` for long-lived architecture decisions. Root `MEMORY.md` is only a template file for target projects, not the preferred place for this repository's own decisions.
- After major decisions, deep bug fixes, or repeated-failure resolutions, proactively suggest a concise update to the appropriate file.
- Keep notes short, clear, and easy for agents to scan. Prefer bullets over long prose.
- Never store secrets, credentials, private tokens, or long transcripts in these files.
- Write project memory in English unless the project explicitly chooses another language.
